    "created_at": "2016-08-22T16:59:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-22T17:00:53Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Minelayers' abscense is noticable on big team and choke maps since constant action makes mine laying redundant. On maps with larger areas per player, Minelayers are actually starting being used to delay attacks and narrow down attack routes.\n\nShifting the role of the engineer from engi-cap-canceling to an utility unit is not really a bad idea. Using engineers as a mine detector would allow players to avoid building a Minelayer simply to detect mines after which the unit is discarded or put to use laying its own mines by whim because, well, now you have a Minelayer.\n\nEngineers are cheaper and more available, but as opposed to the Minelayer it's slow, fragile and will still die if walking over or standing next to an exploding mine field.\n"
  },
